<div class="ec-container">
  <div class="ec-header">
    <h1 class="ec-title">Edge Computing: The Brain on the Factory Floor</h1>
    <p class="ec-subtitle">Why sending all your data to the cloud is no longer sustainable for modern manufacturing.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="ec-main">
    <p class="ec-text">
      As factories become "smarter," they generate an astronomical amount of data. Sending terabytes of high-frequency sensor data to the cloud for processing introduces latency, consumes massive bandwidth, and poses security risks. The solution? Edge computing.
    </p>

    <div class="ec-compare">
      <div class="ec-side ec-cloud">
        <h3 class="ec-h3">Cloud Computing</h3>
        <ul class="ec-list">
          <li>High Latency (milliseconds to seconds)</li>
          <li>High Bandwidth Costs</li>
          <li>Dependent on internet connectivity</li>
          <li>Best for long-term analytics & training</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ec-side ec-edge">
        <h3 class="ec-h3">Edge Computing</h3>
        <ul class="ec-list">
          <li>Ultra-Low Latency (microseconds)</li>
          <li>Low Bandwidth Costs</li>
          <li>Operates completely offline</li>
          <li>Best for real-time control & safety</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="ec-h2">Real-Time Decision Making</h2>
    <p class="ec-text">
      By placing computing power directly on or near the machine (the "edge"), AI models can evaluate data instantly. This allows a robotic arm to adjust its trajectory in real-time, or a machine to shut down milliseconds before a catastrophic jam occurs.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

